description.narrative: Children, adolescents, their families and communities, especially the most vulnerable, develop life and self-care skills in harmonious and protective family and community environments that foster positive behavior to prevent violence, abuse and exploitation., which contributes to Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development, Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development (Covid), Gender Discriminatory Roles And Practices. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2023, children and adolescents, especially the most vulnerable, will grow up in a protective environment that fosters the restitution of rights against all types of violence, abuse and exploitation
